ithout the expression \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἐνθάδε κεῖται\u003C/span> and with only the name of the deceased followed by the date of death (expressed with the aorist of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">τελευτάω\u003C/span>) and occasionally the age (but not in this case): e.g. IG 14.551 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001370\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001370\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":303,"html":304},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Amico 1741 276 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 263 no.10 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 281 no.10 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrara 1829 392 no.8 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kirchhoff 1877 9511 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">565\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 215 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":306,"html":307},"handnote","\u003Cp>Regular letters, lunate Ε, cursive Ω, A and Δ with extended serifs.\u003C/p> 